-- Italian Finance Police Find $27 Billion in Untaxed Income in Five Months
-- Lorenzo Totaro
-- 2010-06-22T09:18:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/italian-finance-police-discover-27-billion-in-untaxed-income-in-5-months.html

          
          
             Italian finance police discovered 22
billion euros in undeclared income in the first five months of
2010, according to an e-mailed statement from Rome today.  
 Finance police also identified 3.1 billion euros in unpaid
value-added tax and 4.3 billion euros in “international tax
evasion” during the same period, according to the statement.  
